      <p>Rose, thanks for reporting back on your recipe-trying adventures!  I&#8217;m so glad to hear that the meatballs were a success!  I&#8217;ve got a few in my freezer, and they&#8217;re sounding awfully good right now.  As for the salad dressing, keep in mind that vinegar varies in strength, so one red wine vinegar could be very different from another.  I&#8217;ve been using Beaufor brand, which is relatively cheap but still decent.  You could also try the dressing formula with Champagne vinegar or Sherry vinegar, both delicious as well.</p>
